Tom,<br><br>
I once had the pleasure of attending the Appalachian Fair somewhere near Bristol, TN, a number of years ago, and I felt right at home.<br><br>
I guess my Maine &quot;back kingdom&quot; upbringing is still with me. I would go back on the drop of a dime if I could. Something about Grange suppers, berry picking on the slopes of Tumbledown with the bears, and the warm glow of kerosene lamps from windows full of plants. Indulge my backward glance. Things and people change, but old feelings somehow don't. It is the connection with the people and the place that is important. <br><br>
Yuppie, self centered, status conscious, ego-centric &quot;pretty&quot; phoneys are not in my book. <br><br>
These feelings are from the &quot;before 'Nam&quot; time of my life. I try to connect with them often.
